The ridge of the trochlea on a humerus lies in the middle of the distal end of a humerus on the lateral side of the trochlea and the medial side of the capitulum (capitellum).
The tibial tuberosity is on the anterior side of a tibia and is where a patella ligament attaches.
The articular surface of a talus that interacts with a tibia. It has a deep depression that forms the trochlear groove and is bounded by the medial and lateral condyles.
The furrow between the lateral and medial condyles of the trochlea of talus.
An articular prominence of a talus that engages with the tibia.
The medial condyle of talus is an articular prominence of bone on medial side of the trochlea of a talus, which engages with the tibia.
The lateral condyle of talus is an articular prominence of bone on the lateral side of the trochlea of a talus, which engages with the tibia.

A depression that runs between the two facets of a talus that interact with a calcaneum.

An anatomical structure that protrudes from the head region. In vertebrates, this includes the part of the cranium (skull) in front of the zygomatic arches that also holds the teeth, palat, and nasal cavity. In invertebrates it is the forward extension of the carapace and/or the piercing mouthparts.
Nasal bone on the left side of an organism when in anatomical position.
Nasal bone on the right side of an organism when in anatomical position.
Zygomatic arch on the left side of an organism when in anatomical position.
Zygomatic arch on the right side of an organism when in anatomical position.
A condyle on the distal end and lateral side of a radius.
A condyle on the distal end and medial side of a radius that interacts with the ulna.
The articular surface on the distal end of a radius that interacts with carpals.
